    "poi_id": 1,
    "description": "Our first stop is the old Patto bridge. This bridge was built it in 1632 i.e. its more than 450 years old. It was built using locally available laterite stone after hardening the soil below using wooden logs. It was actually extension of the Ponte De Linhares which connected Panjim to Ribandar. After the liberation it came to know as Patto Bridge and the area around it is Patto. There is new Patto Bridge which got constructed much later."
