    "title": "The 31st January road ",
    "poi_id": 9,
    "description": "The 31st January road or Rua 31 de Janeira commemorates the historic liberation of Portugal from Spain on 31 January, 1640. It was on this day that Spanish rule was overthrown in a Bloodless coup and the Duke  of Braganca was proclaimed as the King of Portugal with the title King John IV. This Street is filled with wax merchants, petty tradesmen and wine merchants. When settlers from up the river Mandovi first occupied Panaji, this street was given to bakers, candle-makers and wine merchants."
